      p Grafana is most commonly used for visualizing time series data for <strong>Internet infrastructure</strong> and <strong>application analytics</strong> but many use it in other domains including <strong>industrial sensors</strong>, <strong>home automation</strong>, <srong>weather</strong>, and <strong>process control</strong>.

      p Grafana features pluggable panels and data sources allowing easy extensibility and a variety of panels, including fully featured graph panels with rich visualization options. There is currently support for <a href="#">Graphite</a>, <a href="#">InfluxDB</a>, <a href="#">OpenTSDB</a> and <a href="#">KairosDB</a>, and support for <a href="#">SQL</a> is on the roadmap.
